reviewText: VHS tapes arrived in fine shape n plays fine.
If not Gassman this would have bombed

I saw this movie on TV. It was hilarious. I wanted to buy it but couldn't find anything other than this copy. It's was pricey but I said "hey it's a great and apparently RARE movie to find." Sadly, it is an incredibly awful transfer. Very disappointing. If you really want to watch it then you have no choice it seems than this version. Bummer. Not worth it for the price.

It is very insulting to Ann-Margret and her longtime fans for a video company like Koch Music to misspell her name on the cover.  She has been in the business for over 50 years!  You would think that would be long enough for people to know how she spells her name.

Besides Ann Margaret and her Italian co-star, it has a beautiful metallic blue Ferrari, either a 330 GTC or Super America. It would be a 1966 or 67 model. I will wait until the price of the DVD goes down a bit.
